Aspen, Colorado imposes a 40% tax on tobacco and nicotine products.4 All tobacco product retailers must first obtain a license to sell, offer for sale, or exchange for any form of consideration a tobacco product.

Boulder, Colorado imposes a 40% sales and use tax on electronic smoking devices, refills, cartridges, and components.6 Effective January 1, 2021, the city of Boulder adopted a new law requiring any person conducting “business of offering or selling tobacco products” to first obtain a license.
